This paper deals with the problem of computing Walrasian equilibrium in an economy with indivisible goods and general buyer valuations. This problem is a fundamental topic in computational economics and game theory, and is closely related to several subfields of computer science. The paper uses techniques from convex optimization, subgradient methods, and value oracle models, which are commonly used in the areas of algorithms, optimization, and complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.GT (Computational Geometry and Topology), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.EC (Economics and Computation), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
